args: Good boy. Give me the letter.
Never thought the day'd come when I saw\na duskhawk with my own eyes.
Oh, nothin'. Just thought maybe you and\nme could wag jaws for a spell.
Duskhawks are said to be bad luck 'cause\nthey fly at night, yeah?
Indeed. It's said that when a duskhawk \nflies through the night sky, people die.
That's 'cause assassin guilds use 'em as\nmessengers, yeah?
So! Hard at work tonight, are we?
What are you trying to imply?
Imply? This is me bein' straightforward!\nBut hey, lemme try again...
Who ya off to kill, Reaper?
...So you know that name, do you?
I've been a mercenary for a long time.\nYa hear all kinds'a stories in this line\nof work.
One of 'em was about a master assassin\nwho always takes out his targets with a\nsingle arrow.
His name was Hawk, but apparently some\nfolks called him the Reaper.
So spit it out, Reaper. Who's your target? \n'Cause if it's {player_name} or\nany of the others in the castle—
If you're so curious, come with me.
Come watch ya kill somebody? No thanks.
If you're unhappy with what you witness,\nyou can stop me or do whatever you like.
...So what're we doin' in the middle of a\nforest? Tree tick ya off?
*sigh* Well, looks like ya ain't after\nfolks from the castle, so that's somethin'.
Time for what? I don't see nothin'.
What're ya gettin' yer bow ready for?\nI can't see a damn thing!
C'mon, ya can't just shoot arrows off into\nthe middle of nowhere like—
Where the hell did THAT come from?!
My aim was true. With me, Ranzal.
Guess I'm already into this thing up to\nmy eyeballs...
That arrow pierced your femoral region.\nYou'll be going nowhere.
D-damn it... No one warned me I was\ngonna run into a guy like this...
I'll treat you this time, but this is your only\nwarning. Next time, my arrow will pierce\nyour forehead.
He was an assassin from the guild.
Buh?! How do you know that?!
Because I have an ally within the guild\nwho informs me if the guild receives any\nrequests on {player_name}'s life.
So THAT'S what that duskhawk came for!
Sheesh... I've made one hell of a\nmisunderstandin' here. Sorry 'bout that.
Any who knew my name would assume\nthe same.
Yeah, I guess. But to tell the truth,\nsomethin' still don't feel right here.
Why would someone with a nickname like\n＂Reaper＂ be helpin' folks like us?
All my life, I have believed survival of the\nfittest to be the natural way of the world\nfor man and beast alike.
I believed it common sense that I could\nonly live on through the deaths of others.
But I learned of someone who believed it\nwrong for the world to act in such a way.
Correct. He seeks to create a world\nwithout victims.
Some might consider his words to be\nsomething out of a faerie tale...
I still don't fully believe it's possible.\nBut if such a world DID exist,\nI would want to see it.
So until he has a chance to realize his\ndream, I don't want him to die.
And then, one day, I hope a Reaper like\nme is no longer needed in this world.
